2 unit(s) Ciabatta
2 sachet(s) Sun Dried Tomato Paste
1 sachet(s) Olives
50 grams Grated Cheese
90 grams Chorizo
2 unit(s) Tomato
to taste Salt
to taste Pepper
to taste Sugar

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.
Roughly chop the olives.
Roughly chop the tomatoes.
In a bowl, toss together olives, tomato and chorizo. Season with salt, pepper and sugar.

Halve your ciabatta. Pop onto a lined baking tray (cut-side up).
Spread the sun dried tomato paste over the bread.
Top with the chorizo mix and scatter over the cheese.
Bake on the top shelf of the oven until the cheese has melted and the edges are starting to crisp, 8-10 mins.

Once cooked carefully remove the topped ciabatta from the oven.
Pop onto a sharing board and cut into small triangles.